{"id":"everlasting","term":"Everlasting","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Eternal, applied to God (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 21:33\">Gen. 21:33</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 33:27\">Deut. 33:27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 41:13\">Ps. 41:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 90:2\">90:2</a>). We also read of the “everlasting hills” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 49:26\">Gen. 49:26</a>); an “everlasting priesthood” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 40:15\">Ex. 40:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 25:13\">Num. 25:13</a>). (See ETERNAL.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 21:33","Deuteronomy 33:27","Psalms 41:13","Psalms 90:2","Genesis 49:26","Exodus 40:15","Numbers 25:13"]}